Mark your calendars for September 26th - 6 PM!

Come join Gunter High School Chamber Choir for our Character Night Dinner on Saturday, September 26 at 6:00PM in the GHS Commons!

Meet your favorite characters from ‚ÄúFrozen‚Äù, ‚ÄúThe Little Mermaid‚Äù, ‚ÄúNightmare Before Christmas‚Äù, ‚ÄúHeathers: The Musical‚Äù, and more! Individually boxed dinners will be catered by Vitinas Deli and Boiler Room. Tickets are $15 for adults, $10 for kids 12 and under, and free for children under 2. Tickets are available at https://www.gunterisd.org/finearts.

** Please note, due to COVID guidelines, all audience members must wear an appropriate face covering, and tickets will not be sold at the door. We can‚Äôt wait to see you there!

***The deadline to purchase tickets is September 24th.

Hi Tiger Family! First - I want to extend a HUGE thank you to everyone! I know we shared a LOT of information in our Back-to-School Plan earlier this month and I know there are many more things we still need to answer.

I wanted to let you know that there will be communication coming early next week with more details (info about Remote Learning, play-by-play on Weeks 1, 2 & 3 which are a little different, details on Meet the Teacher and Open House and First Day of School logistics). All of that and MORE...

Hang with us as our team has been doing some heavy lifting with changing guidance and intense planning to prepare for this unique year! You all have been so gracious and supportive and we are THANKFUL for you! School Starts August 19th & 20th!

Have a question? Drop it in the comments below and we'll try to include it in our communication to you!

www.gunterisd.org/backtoschool2020

Congratulations to Cassady Craddock for receiving the Texas FFA San Antonio Livestock Show and Rodeo scholarship!

This is a prestigious scholarship valued at $20,000. Competition for the award is fierce and takes many years of involvement in FFA along with academic success in school to be awarded this honor.

Cassady willl be recognized during the 4th General Session of the Texas FFA Virtual Convention on Thursday, July 9th. You may tune in live at 3 PM to view the award ceremony at this link: convention.texasffa.org

Congratulations to Gunter FFA Members, Gunnar and Bethany, who qualified for STATE in their Prepared Public Speaking competition. These students wrote, memorized and delivered a 6-8 minute speech to a panel of judges. The presentation was conducted online due to the COVID virus.

- Senior Prepared Ag Technology & Communications- 1st Place Area V, 1st Place District III

- Senior Prepared Plant Science - 1st Place Area V, 1st Place District III

Bethany Martinek
- Soil Stewardship 1st Place Area V, 1st Place District III

The State FFA Convention in July will also be held online this year, and the State Qualifiers will again compete via Zoom.

We are proud to have you representing Gunter FFA!

Hi Gunter Families! Earlier this morning we shared a survey with our GISD families about next year. There are several key decisions that will dictate what next year looks like ‚Äì some of which we WILL have control over (ie, how we choose to use hand sanitizer or if/whether we take daily temperatures) and some we may not have control over (ie, whether 6 feet of space is required).

We are HOPEFUL that as the state continues to re-open, we will be able to bring all students back together on August 19th. But we also want to get feedback to help make decisions that are reflective of our community for every area for which we get to decide.

Thanks in advance for completing your survey! If you did not receive our email through the School Messenger system, please drop a note with your students names & grade levels and your email to jsiler@gunterisd.org and we‚Äôll fix it in our systems. If you are NEW to GISD and not yet in our systems, please email jsiler@gunterisd.org and we'll forward it to you. Thanks!
text:

We are HOPEFUL that as the state continues to re-open, we will be able to bring all students back together on August 19th. But we also want to get feedback to help make decisions that are reflective of our community for every area for which we get to decide.

Thanks in advance for completing your survey! If you did not receive our email through the School Messenger system, please drop a note with your students names & grade levels and your email to jsiler@gunterisd.org and we‚Äôll fix it in our systems. Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) is a one-time food benefit for families who lost access to free or reduced-price meals due to school closures.

Eligible P-EBT families will receive application instructions from schools in late May. The P-EBT application will open the first week of June.

P-EBT food benefits are for children who received SNAP food benefits for March 2020 and children who are certified for free or reduced-price school meals during the 2019-20 Texas school year. For more information, visit: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT

Please contact Lauren Rogers, Child Nutrition Director, at (903) 696-1310 or lrogers@gunterisd.org with any questions.

post_text: You‚Äôve heard of Flat Stanley, but have you heard of Flat Mrs. Harper? Well, Mrs. Harper‚Äôs 1st grade students have! The students had a ‚ÄúFlat Mrs. Harper‚Äù that they took on adventures while they were in COVID 19 Quarantine. You can see that Mrs. Harper enjoyed many adventures, some of which were reading on the couch, eating a fun lunch, and paddle boating. Who knows... maybe Flat Mrs. Harper will continue to go places with her students this summer and beyond! This was a great way for her students to keep her close to their hearts.

post_text:
We had amazing weather to deliver caps/gowns, graduation instructions, roses, and an envelope with special messages to each senior in the Class of 2020. The administration team divided into 2 suburbans and traveled to each of the seniors homes to make this special delivery today. It was amazing to see the smiling faces of those who were home. We were sad to have missed some of you. We were also happy to be greeted by many family pets!
Once we gather all of the photos, we will place them in a central location where you can download your picture.

post_text:
Internet Update: We wanted to share information about the two major outages with Suddenlink this past week (April 21 / 28). We wanted to let you know that this was connected to a regional project that is bringing fiber from Dallas to Grayson County to increase connectivity for rural districts. The subcontractors for that group inadvertently severed Suddenlink's line on two separate occasions. We have been in touch with that company and they have assured us that they have multiple safeguards in place from preventing this from occurring again in the future. Both Suddenlink and the City of Gunter have been proactive in helping find the source of this problem.

Our remote learning is set up such that every assignment has a 1-week window for completion (with an additional 1-week window of grace beyond that) so please don't stress about due dates. üëå

Our 4th Grade had a SUPER SPECIAL guest read to them today during their class meeting. Margaret Peterson Haddix has written more than 40 books for kids and teens, including Running Out of Time; Double Identity; Uprising; The Always War; the Greystone Secrets series; the Shadow Children series; the Missing series; the Children of Exile series; the Under Their Skin duology; and The Palace Chronicles. She also wrote Into the Gauntlet, the tenth book in the 39 Clues series. Her books have been honored with New York Times bestseller status, the International Reading Association‚Äôs Children‚Äôs Book Award; American Library Association Best Book and Quick Pick for Reluctant Young Adult Readers notations; and numerous state reader‚Äôs choice awards. Today she read from the book "Found" which is part of "The Missing Series".

Special thanks to Mrs. Johnson, GES Librarian, for setting up this outstanding event for the kids!

post_text:
The GISD nurses wanted to pass along this resource for Telemedicine. Virtual Visit can be used for both you and your children. They can see you for most illnesses at this time:) This includes cold/flu, strep, asthma, pink eye, complications with allergies, skin rashes, possible infections on the skin, and even UTI symptoms. If you think you have signs or symptoms of COVID-19 you can schedule a visit and they have doctors that can screen your symptoms and refer you and/or your children to the appropriate place for testing and treatment.

Virtual Visit is an app that you can put on your smartphone or computer and use your camera/video to talk with nurses and doctors.

If you have any questions/concerns OR if we can help in any way during this time, please email your campus nurse at anytime.

Nurse Casey - GES - clayman@gunterisd.org
Nurse Thomas - GMS - nthomas@gunterisd.org
Nurse Clarke - GHS - jclarke@gunterisd.org

Visit childrens.com/virtualvisit for more information

The library offers free wifi to the public as well as multiple computers for use. In the event that schools are postponed longer than this week, the library will remain open and offer extended hours by appointment for students who need internet access to complete homework assignments. The free wifi is available to all and can be access from the parking lot on mobile devices if patrons wish to keep a distance from others.

post_text:
We are so thankful for all of you who have reached out to help provide food for some of our families during this time of unexpected closure.

Gunter ISD will be serving Grab & Go meals daily for all students, PK-12, from 11am-1pm at GES starting Monday, March 16th. Families can drive or walk up to the normal drop-off zone at GES to pick up lunch and breakfast for the following day.

In addition to free meals, GISD has been working with community partners and the Gunter Food Pantry to provide groceries to families during this time. They are currently gathering food and donations for this initiative.

The Gunter Food Pantry will be open on Tuesday, March 17th from 11:00am-2:00pm for grocery pick-up and GISD will be working to deliver food later next week as well to families who are unable to stop by on Tuesday.

Please join this Facebook page for more information on how to donate or get involved: https://www.facebook.com/groups/2511562255727014/

post_text:
Gunter ISD will remain closed from March 16-20 in an attempt to minimize the health and safety risks to our community from the coronavirus. Please know that students are always at the heart of our decisions, and we are managing this situation with them and our entire community in mind.

The district will continue to monitor and evaluate the situation prior to reopening school on Monday, March 23, and will communicate across all channels as updated information becomes available. During this extended spring break, district offices and campuses will be closed and most events will be cancelled or postponed. Please read the letter for more information.

The high school art students competed in their first ever UIL competition this past Saturday. They competed against 5A and 6A schools and proved that our 3A school has just as much talent!

35 schools competed, 2084 artworks entered; 23 of those entries came from Gunter. Out of the 23, 16 received the highest rating of 4, and the other 7 received the 2nd highest rating of 3! Our students did an excellent job of presenting their art during the interview portion and all came out of their interview excited.
Congratulations to the following artists!

Hello Tiger Nation! The state championship tumblers are ready to order. This year, we included as many players, staff, and support personnel as possible. If your child was involved, there is a good chance her or his name is on the cup. To order the cup and savor the memory go to:

http://fund.school/gunterfootball

There you will be able to order the Gunter Tiger State Championship tumbler as well as scroll through cups branded by your favorite professional sports teams. It‚Äôs all online and your cup(s) will be shipped to you directly. A portion of the proceeds does come back to the school to benefit the student-athletes and their future endeavors. Thank you for your continued support and Go Tigers!

Tonight was a great night at GISD! We celebrated so many people at the board meeting, it was incredible. We would like to thank Natalee Hayes for opening our meeting. After that, we were excited to announce the Superintendent Honor Roll recipients and the 20/20 Vision Staff Awards. Finally, we had 3 groups of outstanding students who were recognized in front of the school board for their top notch accomplishments.
Congratulations to everyone!

Superintendent Honor Roll
Elementary - Brinley Beavers and Stone Rumage
Middle School - Luzcero Escalera and Gavin Dupler
High School - Hailey Wilde and Jack Locke

post_text: Mrs. Bon's 5th grade science class has been learning about erosion. They have been following a 50 pound salt cube that has a slow drip running over it. The erosion is magnificent! The students also mimicked different types of erosion in the lab using dirt, sand, sugar and water. They were able to see how water, wind and motion affect the earth.

post_text:
Sewing? Yes! These Advanced Animal Science students had to practice their fancy stitch work today. This is not "stitching" as in sewing a garment, they were practicing putting sutures into animals. (No animals were injured in this exercise... they used mats that simulate the skin.)

Wow! We are impressed with their steady hand and pretty stitches!

To begin our school board meeting tonight, the board members were showered with gifts of appreciation from the students and faculty of GISD. Special thanks to Schuylar Marshall for opening the meeting. Once the meeting began, each campus had gifts to present. It would be impossible to mention all of the gifts, but the pictures will show you how much our students, faculty and community love our board members.
#schoolboardappreciationmonth

post_text: Tonight the GES PTO and the GHS PTO combined forces to show appreciation to our GISD School Board by preparing a meal and ordering flowers from our own Tiger Floral to decorate the tables. The menu included homemade lasagna and pasta, salad and breadsticks. The dessert table was nothing less than impressive! Everything tasted amazing and it was a great way to begin the meeting. Thank you so much for spoiling our leaders tonight!

post_text: Gunter FFA students had the opportunity to meet and visit with two State Officers last week. They presented the 3 P's (Perspective, People and Performance) which taught our students how to exhibit confidence in all that they do. The students were involved in several activities to help them understand the concept, and then ended with a Q&A about the duties and responsibilities of a State FFA Officer. The visit was very educational, and we were lucky to host them here at GHS!

Kindergarteners in Mrs. Keel‚Äôs class spent the week learning about ways to make their community better. They read the book, ‚ÄúRoadwork,‚Äù and learned about different machines that are used to build a road.

Today, through the use of technology, Mr. Keel (you can see him pictured below) took them on a virtual field trip to Southwest Erosion Control where he showed them some of the heavy equipment they had been learning about. As you can see in their faces, they loved getting to meet him and actually see the big truck and other equipment!

post_text:
The GHS cheerleaders are in Fort Worth to compete for the UIL Spirit State Championship! If you attended the 2nd Annual Showcase, you already know how GREAT they are! If you want to support them at competition, please check out the schedule below. Special thanks to the band and middle school cheerleaders who will attend as a group to yell LOUD & PROUD for the girls! Good Luck GHS Cheerleaders, your fellow TIGERS are cheering for YOU!

The schedule for UIL State (Jan 16 at the Ft Worth CC):
Thursday January 16th ‚Äì GAME DAY!
8:44 am Fight Song
9:44 am Crowd Leading
10:59 am Band Chant
11:50-12:00 Announcement of Top 20 group 1 (we have to be in the top 20 here to have a shot at the finals later in the day)
3:50-4:00 Announcement of 3A Finalists
5:15 pm 3A FINALS
7:45 pm Awards Ceremony
Tickets are $15 Adult/$10 Student.
Link to UIL State Spirit Competition info: https://www.uiltexas.org/spirit/spirit-state-championships
